LANYARD POWER HOLDINGS, LLC
Market-Based Rate Tariff
1. Availability: Lanyard Power Holdings, LLC ("Lanyard Power Holdings" or "Seller") makes electric energy, capacity and ancillary services available under this tariff to any purchaser for resale. The following RTO/ISO specific ancillary services will be made available by Lanyard Power Holdings.
PJM: Lanyard Power Holdings, LLC offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection.
New York: Lanyard Power Holdings, LLC offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc.
Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.
2. Applicability: This tariff is applicable to all sales of energy, capacity, or Ancillary Services by Lanyard Power Holdings not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Lanyard Power Holdings.
3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Lanyard Power Holdings.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Lanyard Power Holdings, LLC.
5. Effective Date: This tariff is effective as of the date specified by the Commission.
6. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Lanyard Power Holdings shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Lanyard Power Holdings does not have any limitations on its market-based rate authority. The Commission has granted Lanyard Power Holdings, LLC in Southern Company Energy Marketing, L.P., et al., Docket No. ER00-3760-000 at Appendix A (November 21, 2000) (unpublished letter order), the following exemptions: (i) waivers of Parts 41, 101 (with the exception that waiver of the provisions that apply to hydropower licensees has not been granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects) and 141 of the Commission's accounting and periodic reporting requirements (except for sections 141.14 and 141.15), (ii) waivers of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except as to sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16, and (iii) blanket authorization for all future issuances of securities or assumptions of liabilities pursuant to Section 204 of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. ? 824e, and Part 34 of the Commission's regulations.
8. Seller Category: Lanyard Power Holdings is a Category 2 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ?35.36(a), in the Northeast region, and a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ?35.36(a), in the Central, Northwest, Southeast, Southwest and Southwest Power Pool regions.

LANYARD POWER HOLDINGS, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1 Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service Lanyard Power Holdings, LLC ("Lanyard Power Holdings") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Chalk Point generation facility ("Facility") within the Potomac Electric Power Company zone under the operational control of PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Lanyard Power Holdings' revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Facility for the units set forth below. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Lanyard Power Holdings' monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the sum of the charges for the Facility's units specified below.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Chalk Point Unit Monthly Revenue Requirement CT 1 $1,725.50 Total Monthly Revenue Requirement $1,725.50 Total Annual (Total Monthly x 12) $20,706.00
PARTIAL MONTH REVENUE REQUIREMENT: When a unit deactivation date ("Unit Deactivation Date") is other than the first day of the month, the revenue requirement shall be a blended revenue requirement for the month of service in which the deactivation occurred as follows: the sum of (i) the total monthly revenue requirement prior to the rate change divided by the number of days in the month of the deactivation, with the quotient then multiplied by the number of days in the month prior to the Unit Deactivation Date and (ii) the total monthly revenue requirement after the rate change divided by the number of days in the month of the deactivation, with the quotient then multiplied by the remaining number of days in the month from and including the Unit Deactivation Date.
